</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Chest Fly Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Lie flat on a bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended above your chest, palms facing each other.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbells in an arc to your sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows.</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbells until you feel a deep stretch in your chest, but avoid going too far to prevent shoulder strain.</li>



<li>Bring the dumbbells back up in the same arc motion, squeezing your chest at the top of the movement.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep a slight bend in your elbows to avoid shoulder strain.</li>



<li>Focus on slow, controlled movements to maximize muscle tension.</li>



<li>Avoid letting the dumbbells drop too low, as this can strain the shoulders.</li>



<li>Squeeze your chest muscles at the top of the movement for extra activation.</li>



<li>Use lighter weights and focus on form rather than heavy lifting.</li>
</ul>



